[{"text": "Delighted to be here", "start": 15.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and to talk to you about a subject dear to my heart,", "start": 18.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "which is beauty.", "start": 20.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "I do the philosophy of art, aesthetics,", "start": 23.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "actually, for a living.", "start": 26.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I try to figure out intellectually,", "start": 28.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "philosophically, psychologically,", "start": 30.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "what the experience of beauty is,", "start": 32.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "what sensibly can be said about it", "start": 35.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and how people go off the rails in trying to understand it.", "start": 38.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Now this is an extremely complicated subject,", "start": 41.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "in part because the things that we call beautiful", "start": 44.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "are so different.", "start": 47.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I mean just think of the sheer variety --", "start": 49.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "a baby's face,", "start": 51.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Berlioz's \"Harold in Italy,\"", "start": 53.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "movies like \"The Wizard of Oz\"", "start": 55.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "or the plays of Chekhov,", "start": 57.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "a central California landscape,", "start": 59.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "a Hokusai view of Mt. Fuji,", "start": 61.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "\"Der Rosenkavalier,\"", "start": 64.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "a stunning match-winning goal", "start": 66.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in a World Cup soccer match,", "start": 68.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Van Gogh's \"Starry Night,\"", "start": 70.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "a Jane Austen novel,", "start": 72.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Fred Astaire dancing across the screen.", "start": 74.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "This brief list includes human beings,", "start": 77.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "natural landforms,", "start": 80.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "works of art and skilled human actions.", "start": 82.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "An account that explains the presence of beauty", "start": 85.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "in everything on this list", "start": 88.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is not going to be easy.", "start": 90.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I can, however, give you at least a taste", "start": 92.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "of what I regard", "start": 95.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "as the most powerful theory of beauty", "start": 97.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "we yet have.", "start": 99.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And we get it not from a philosopher of art,", "start": 101.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "not from a postmodern art theorist", "start": 103.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "or a bigwig art critic.", "start": 105.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "No, this theory", "start": 107.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "comes from an expert", "start": 109.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "on barnacles and worms and pigeon breeding,", "start": 111.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and you know who I mean:", "start": 117.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Charles Darwin.", "start": 120.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Of course, a lot of people think they already know", "start": 122.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "the proper answer to the question,", "start": 125.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "\"What is beauty?\"", "start": 128.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It's in the eye of the beholder.", "start": 131.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It's whatever moves you personally.", "start": 133.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Or, as some people,", "start": 135.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "especially academics prefer,", "start": 137.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "beauty is in the culturally conditioned", "start": 139.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "eye of the beholder.", "start": 142.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "People agree that paintings or movies or music", "start": 144.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "are beautiful", "start": 147.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "because their cultures determine a uniformity of aesthetic taste.", "start": 149.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "Taste for both natural beauty and for the arts", "start": 153.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "travel across cultures", "start": 156.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "with great ease.", "start": 158.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Beethoven is adored in Japan.", "start": 160.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Peruvians love Japanese woodblock prints.", "start": 162.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Inca sculptures are regarded as treasures", "start": 165.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in British museums,", "start": 167.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "while Shakespeare is translated", "start": 169.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "into every major language of the Earth.", "start": 171.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Or just think about American jazz", "start": 174.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "or American movies --", "start": 176.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "they go everywhere.", "start": 178.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "There are many differences among the arts,", "start": 180.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "but there are also universal,", "start": 183.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "cross-cultural aesthetic pleasures", "start": 185.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and values.", "start": 187.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "How can we explain", "start": 189.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "this universality?", "start": 192.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "The best answer lies in trying to reconstruct", "start": 195.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "a Darwinian evolutionary history", "start": 197.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "of our artistic and aesthetic tastes.", "start": 200.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "We need to reverse-engineer", "start": 203.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "our present artistic tastes and preferences", "start": 205.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and explain how they came", "start": 208.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to be engraved in our minds", "start": 210.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "by the actions of both our prehistoric,", "start": 213.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "largely pleistocene environments,", "start": 216.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "where we became fully human,", "start": 218.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "but also by the social situations", "start": 220.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in which we evolved.", "start": 222.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "This reverse engineering", "start": 224.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "can also enlist help", "start": 226.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "from the human record", "start": 229.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "preserved in prehistory.", "start": 231.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I mean fossils, cave paintings and so forth.", "start": 233.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And it should take into account", "start": 236.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "what we know of the aesthetic interests", "start": 238.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of isolated hunter-gatherer bands", "start": 240.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "that survived into the 19th and the 20th centuries.", "start": 243.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Now, I personally", "start": 247.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "have no doubt whatsoever", "start": 249.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that the experience of beauty,", "start": 251.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "with its emotional intensity and pleasure,", "start": 253.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "belongs to our evolved human psychology.", "start": 256.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "The experience of beauty is one component", "start": 260.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "in a whole series of Darwinian adaptations.", "start": 263.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Beauty is an adaptive effect,", "start": 267.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "which we extend", "start": 269.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and intensify", "start": 271.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in the creation and enjoyment", "start": 273.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of works of art and entertainment.", "start": 275.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "As many of you will know,", "start": 279.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "evolution operates by two main primary mechanisms.", "start": 281.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "The first of these is natural selection --", "start": 284.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "that's random mutation and selective retention --", "start": 287.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "along with our basic anatomy and physiology --", "start": 290.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "the evolution of the pancreas or the eye or the fingernails.", "start": 293.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Natural selection also explains", "start": 296.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "many basic revulsions,", "start": 299.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "such as the horrid smell of rotting meat,", "start": 301.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "or fears, such as the fear of snakes", "start": 303.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "or standing close to the edge of a cliff.", "start": 306.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Natural selection also explains pleasures --", "start": 309.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "sexual pleasure,", "start": 312.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "our liking for sweet, fat and proteins,", "start": 314.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "which in turn explains a lot of popular foods,", "start": 317.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "from ripe fruits through chocolate malts", "start": 320.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and barbecued ribs.", "start": 323.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "The other great principle of evolution", "start": 326.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is sexual selection,", "start": 328.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and it operates very differently.", "start": 330.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The peacock's magnificent tail", "start": 332.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "is the most famous example of this.", "start": 335.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "It did not evolve for natural survival.", "start": 338.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "In fact, it goes against natural survival.", "start": 341.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "No, the peacock's tail", "start": 344.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "results from the mating choices", "start": 346.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "made by peahens.", "start": 348.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It's quite a familiar story.", "start": 350.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It's women who actually push history forward.", "start": 352.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Darwin himself, by the way,", "start": 356.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "had no doubts that the peacock's tail", "start": 358.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "was beautiful in the eyes of the peahen.", "start": 360.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "He actually used that word.", "start": 362.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Now, keeping these ideas firmly in mind,", "start": 365.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "we can say that the experience of beauty", "start": 368.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "is one of the ways that evolution has", "start": 371.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "of arousing and sustaining", "start": 374.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "interest or fascination,", "start": 376.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "even obsession,", "start": 378.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in order to encourage us", "start": 380.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "toward making the most adaptive decisions", "start": 382.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "for survival and reproduction.", "start": 385.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Beauty is nature's way", "start": 389.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of acting at a distance,", "start": 391.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "so to speak.", "start": 394.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I mean, you can't expect to eat", "start": 396.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "an adaptively beneficial landscape.", "start": 398.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It would hardly do to eat your baby", "start": 400.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "or your lover.", "start": 402.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "So evolution's trick", "start": 404.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is to make them beautiful,", "start": 406.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to have them exert a kind of magnetism", "start": 408.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to give you the pleasure of simply looking at them.", "start": 411.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Consider briefly an important source of aesthetic pleasure,", "start": 415.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "the magnetic pull", "start": 418.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of beautiful landscapes.", "start": 420.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "People in very different cultures", "start": 422.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "all over the world", "start": 424.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "tend to like a particular kind of landscape,", "start": 426.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "a landscape that just happens to be similar", "start": 429.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to the pleistocene savannas where we evolved.", "start": 432.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "This landscape shows up today", "start": 435.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "on calendars, on postcards,", "start": 437.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "in the design of golf courses and public parks", "start": 440.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and in gold-framed pictures", "start": 443.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that hang in living rooms", "start": 445.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "from New York to New Zealand.", "start": 447.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "It's a kind of Hudson River school landscape", "start": 450.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "featuring open spaces", "start": 453.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of low grasses", "start": 455.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "interspersed with copses of trees.", "start": 457.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "The trees, by the way, are often preferred", "start": 460.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "if they fork near the ground,", "start": 462.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that is to say, if they're trees you could scramble up", "start": 464.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "if you were in a tight fix.", "start": 467.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "The landscape shows the presence", "start": 470.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of water directly in view,", "start": 472.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "or evidence of water in a bluish distance,", "start": 474.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "indications of animal or bird life", "start": 478.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "as well as diverse greenery", "start": 481.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and finally -- get this --", "start": 483.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "a path", "start": 486.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "or a road,", "start": 488.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "perhaps a riverbank or a shoreline,", "start": 490.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "that extends into the distance,", "start": 493.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "almost inviting you to follow it.", "start": 496.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "This landscape type is regarded as beautiful,", "start": 500.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "even by people in countries", "start": 503.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that don't have it.", "start": 505.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The ideal savanna landscape", "start": 507.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is one of the clearest examples", "start": 509.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "where human beings everywhere", "start": 511.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "find beauty", "start": 513.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in similar visual experience.", "start": 515.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "But, someone might argue,", "start": 517.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that's natural beauty.", "start": 519.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "How about artistic beauty?", "start": 521.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Isn't that exhaustively cultural?", "start": 524.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "No, I don't think it is.", "start": 527.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And once again, I'd like to look back to prehistory", "start": 529.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to say something about it.", "start": 532.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It is widely assumed", "start": 534.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that the earliest human artworks", "start": 536.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "are the stupendously skillful cave paintings", "start": 538.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "that we all know from Lascaux", "start": 541.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and Chauvet.", "start": 543.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Chauvet caves", "start": 546.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "are about 32,000 years old,", "start": 548.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "along with a few small, realistic sculptures", "start": 550.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "of women and animals from the same period.", "start": 553.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "But artistic and decorative skills", "start": 560.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "are actually much older than that.", "start": 562.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Beautiful shell necklaces", "start": 566.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that look like something you'd see at an arts and crafts fair,", "start": 568.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "as well as ochre body paint,", "start": 571.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "have been found", "start": 573.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "from around 100,000 years ago.", "start": 575.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "But the most intriguing prehistoric artifacts", "start": 577.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "are older even than this.", "start": 580.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I have in mind", "start": 582.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the so-called Acheulian hand axes.", "start": 584.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "The oldest stone tools are choppers", "start": 588.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "from the Olduvai Gorge in East Africa.", "start": 591.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "They go back about two-and-a-half-million years.", "start": 593.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "These crude tools", "start": 596.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "were around for thousands of centuries,", "start": 598.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "until around 1.4 million years ago", "start": 601.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "when Homo erectus", "start": 604.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "started shaping", "start": 606.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "single, thin stone blades,", "start": 608.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "sometimes rounded ovals,", "start": 610.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "but often in what are to our eyes", "start": 613.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "an arresting, symmetrical pointed leaf", "start": 615.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "or teardrop form.", "start": 618.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "These Acheulian hand axes --", "start": 620.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "they're named after St. Acheul in France,", "start": 622.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "where finds were made in 19th century --", "start": 624.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "have been unearthed in their thousands,", "start": 627.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "scattered across Asia, Europe and Africa,", "start": 630.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "almost everywhere Homo erectus", "start": 633.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and Homo ergaster roamed.", "start": 636.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Now, the sheer numbers of these hand axes", "start": 639.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "shows that they can't have been made", "start": 642.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "for butchering animals.", "start": 644.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And the plot really thickens when you realize", "start": 646.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "that, unlike other pleistocene tools,", "start": 649.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "the hand axes often exhibit", "start": 652.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "no evidence of wear", "start": 654.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "on their delicate blade edges.", "start": 656.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And some, in any event, are too big", "start": 658.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to use for butchery.", "start": 660.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Their symmetry, their attractive materials", "start": 663.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and, above all,", "start": 665.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "their meticulous workmanship", "start": 667.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "are simply quite beautiful", "start": 669.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to our eyes, even today.", "start": 672.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "So what were these ancient --", "start": 675.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "I mean, they're ancient, they're foreign,", "start": 679.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "but they're at the same time", "start": 681.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "somehow familiar.", "start": 683.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "What were these artifacts for?", "start": 685.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "The best available answer", "start": 688.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is that they were literally", "start": 690.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the earliest known works of art,", "start": 692.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "practical tools transformed", "start": 694.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "into captivating aesthetic objects,", "start": 696.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "contemplated both for their elegant shape", "start": 699.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and their virtuoso craftsmanship.", "start": 701.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Hand axes mark", "start": 705.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "an evolutionary advance in human history --", "start": 707.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "tools fashioned to function", "start": 709.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "as what Darwinians call \"fitness signals\" --", "start": 711.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "that is to say, displays", "start": 714.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that are performances", "start": 716.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "like the peacock's tail,", "start": 718.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "except that, unlike hair and feathers,", "start": 720.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "the hand axes are consciously", "start": 723.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "cleverly crafted.", "start": 725.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Competently made hand axes", "start": 727.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "indicated desirable personal qualities --", "start": 729.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "intelligence, fine motor control,", "start": 733.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "planning ability,", "start": 736.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "conscientiousness", "start": 738.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and sometimes access to rare materials.", "start": 740.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Over tens of thousands of generations,", "start": 743.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "such skills increased the status", "start": 746.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of those who displayed them", "start": 748.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and gained a reproductive advantage", "start": 750.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "over the less capable.", "start": 752.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "You know, it's an old line,", "start": 754.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "but it has been shown to work --", "start": 756.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "\"Why don't you come up to my cave, so I can show you my hand axes?\"", "start": 758.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "(Laughter)", "start": 761.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Except, of course, what's interesting about this", "start": 763.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "is that we can't be sure how that idea was conveyed,", "start": 766.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "because the Homo erectus", "start": 769.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that made these objects", "start": 771.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "did not have language.", "start": 774.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It's hard to grasp,", "start": 776.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "but it's an incredible fact.", "start": 778.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "This object was made", "start": 781.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "by a hominid ancestor,", "start": 783.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Homo erectus or Homo ergaster,", "start": 786.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "between 50,000 and 100,000 years", "start": 790.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "before language.", "start": 793.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Stretching over a million years,", "start": 796.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the hand axe tradition", "start": 798.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is the longest artistic tradition", "start": 800.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "in human and proto-human history.", "start": 803.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "By the end of the hand axe epic, Homo sapiens --", "start": 806.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "as they were then called, finally --", "start": 809.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "were doubtless finding new ways", "start": 811.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to amuse and amaze each other", "start": 813.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "by, who knows, telling jokes,", "start": 816.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "storytelling, dancing, or hairstyling.", "start": 818.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Yes, hairstyling -- I insist on that.", "start": 821.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "For us moderns,", "start": 824.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "virtuoso technique", "start": 826.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is used to create imaginary worlds", "start": 828.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in fiction and in movies,", "start": 830.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to express intense emotions", "start": 832.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "with music, painting and dance.", "start": 834.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "But still,", "start": 837.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "one fundamental trait", "start": 839.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of the ancestral personality persists", "start": 841.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in our aesthetic cravings:", "start": 843.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "the beauty we find", "start": 846.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in skilled performances.", "start": 848.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "From Lascaux to the Louvre", "start": 850.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to Carnegie Hall,", "start": 852.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "human beings", "start": 854.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "have a permanent innate taste", "start": 856.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "for virtuoso displays in the arts.", "start": 858.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "We find beauty", "start": 862.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in something done well.", "start": 864.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "So the next time you pass a jewelry shop window", "start": 868.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "displaying a beautifully cut", "start": 870.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "teardrop-shaped stone,", "start": 872.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "don't be so sure", "start": 874.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "it's just your culture telling you", "start": 876.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that that sparkling jewel is beautiful.", "start": 878.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Your distant ancestors loved that shape", "start": 880.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and found beauty in the skill needed to make it,", "start": 883.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "even before", "start": 886.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "they could put their love into words.", "start": 888.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Is beauty in the eye of the beholder?", "start": 890.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "No, it's deep in our minds.", "start": 893.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "It's a gift handed down from the intelligent skills", "start": 896.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and rich emotional lives", "start": 899.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of our most ancient ancestors.", "start": 901.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Our powerful reaction to images,", "start": 904.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to the expression of emotion in art,", "start": 906.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to the beauty of music, to the night sky,", "start": 909.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "will be with us and our descendants", "start": 912.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "for as long as the human race exists.", "start": 915.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Thank you.", "start": 918.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "(Applause)", "start": 920.26, "duration": 7.0}]